episodes.seriesTitle: Good One: A Podcast About Jokes
episodes.title: Weird Al Yankovic's "Word Crimes"
episodes.author: New York Magazine / Panoply
episodes.summary: Weird Al Yankovic explains his parody process and the story behind creating "Word Crimes."

episodes.seriesTitle: Good One: A Podcast About Jokes
episodes.title: Kristen Schaal and Her Singing, Dancing Bird
episodes.author: New York Magazine / Panoply
episodes.summary: Kristen Schaal joins Jesse David Fox to talk about the origins of one of her earliest jokes Dancing Bird. She shares why she often uses animals in her comedy and what it was like to break out as a stand-up comic using conceptual bits.

episodes.seriesTitle: Good One: A Podcast About Jokes
episodes.title: Neal Brennan's White Guy Being Called the N-Word While Feeding a Horse Joke
episodes.author: New York Magazine / Panoply
episodes.summary: Host Jesse David Fox and Neal Brennan talk about a joke Neal wrote for Half Baked and how it's representative of his early career writing for the Chapelle's Show, and Neal shares about his new stand-up special on Netflix 3 Mics.

episodes.seriesTitle: Good One: A Podcast About Jokes
episodes.title: Jim Gaffigan and His Good Looking Newscasters Joke
episodes.author: New York Magazine / Panoply
episodes.summary: Jesse David Fox sits down with Jim Gaffigan to break down a joke from Jim’s Netflix special Cinco about newscasters and how they’re so good looking.

episodes.seriesTitle: Good One: A Podcast About Jokes
episodes.title: Trailer
episodes.author: New York Magazine / Panoply
episodes.summary: Vulture presents Good One: A Podcast About Jokes—  it's about jokes and the people who tell them. Guests include Jim Gaffigan, Kristen Schaal, Paul Feig, Neal Brennan and Paul Scheer. Hosted by Vulture Senior Editor Jesse David Fox, the first episode premieres February 13.
